<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3614917" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="NEW"><variable id="borders"><link href="text/swriter/guide/borders.xhp">User Defined Borders in Text Documents</link>
</variable></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id1069368" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">You can apply a variety of different cell borders to selected cells in a Writer table and to the whole table. Other objects in text documents can have user defined borders, too. For example, you can assign borders to page styles, to frames, and to inserted pictures or charts.</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id6527298" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Select the cell or a block of cells in a Writer table.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id6129947" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Choose <item type="menuitem">Table - Table properties</item>.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id8141117" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">In the dialog, click the <emph>Borders</emph> tab.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id6016418" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Choose the border options you want to apply and click OK.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id5282448" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">The options in the <emph>Line arrangement</emph> area can be used to apply multiple border styles.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3547166" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Selection of cells</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id1108432" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Depending on the selection of cells, the area looks different.</paragraph>
